            <div type="text">
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>[Mr H. P. Lee (letter Jan. 17, 1873) describes a lateral shake of the index finger or of the whole hand as a common sign of negation in Japan.]</p>
<p>[Mr H. P. Lee (letter Jan. 17, 1873) has observed that the intelligent Chinese brought up from boyhood as servants of Europeans blush readily and profusely, <hi rend="underline">e.g.</hi> on being bantered by their masters on their personal appearance.]</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

